# Operator Overloading

## Definition
In C++, when operators are overloaded, they execute **user-defined functions** whenever used, allowing for customized behavior.

---

## Example: Overloading `+` Operator for Complex Numbers

```cpp
class Complex {
public:
    int real, imag;

    Complex(int r = 0, int i = 0) {
        real = r;
        imag = i;
    }

    Complex operator + (const Complex &obj) {
        Complex res;
        res.real = real + obj.real;
        res.imag = imag + obj.imag;
        return res;
    }
};

