# Why const is used?

```cpp
Complex operator+(const Complex &obj) const
```

### First const

```cpp
const Complex &obj
```

Prevents modification of incoming object.

```cpp
obj.real = 100; // Error
```

---

### Second const

```cpp
... ) const
```

Guarantees current object won't change.

```cpp
Complex c1(2,3);

c1 + c2;
```

Addition should not modify `c1`.

