# Runtime Polymorphism Example

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class ComplexOperation
{
public:

    virtual void operation()
    {
        cout<<"Base Operation"<<endl;
    }

    virtual ~ComplexOperation() {}
};

class Addition : public ComplexOperation
{
public:

    void operation() override
    {
        cout<<"Complex Number Addition"<<endl;
    }
};

int main()
{
    ComplexOperation* ptr;

    Addition add;

    ptr = &add;

    ptr->operation();
}
```

Output:

```cpp
Complex Number Addition
```

Because of:

```cpp
virtual
```

Runtime decides which function to call.

