# Most Asked Interview Questions

### Q1 Why is Operator Overloading Compile Time Polymorphism?

Because compiler resolves:

```cpp
c1 + c2
```

to

```cpp
c1.operator+(c2)
```

during compilation.

---

### Q2 Can all operators be overloaded?

No.

```cpp
::
.
.*
?:
sizeof
typeid
```

cannot be overloaded.

---

### Q3 Can we create new operators?

No.

Only existing operators can be overloaded.

---

### Q4 Can precedence change after overloading?

No.

Operator precedence remains same.

---

### Q5 Why use friend for << and >> ?

Because left operand is:

```cpp
cout
```

not Complex object.

So member function won't work naturally.

Hence:

```cpp
friend ostream& operator<<(...)
```

---

### Q6 Difference Between Overloading and Overriding?

| Overloading        | Overriding       |
| ------------------ | ---------------- |
| Compile Time       | Runtime          |
| Same Function Name | Same Signature   |
| Same Class         | Parent-Child     |
| No Virtual Needed  | Virtual Required |

